HTML Cheat Sheet:

Syntax and terms:

HTML means: HyperText Markup Language.
This is not a programming language and strictly for presentation.

files must end with a '.html' extension.
homepage should always be called 'index.html'.

Tag Syntax:
Element names surrounded by angle brackets.
Normally comes in pairs (start tag and end tag)
End tag is usually the same but with a forward slash.
Some tags close themselves (Remnant of XHTML)

Examples:
<tagname>content</tagname>
<h1>About Us</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph</p>
<br/> (self closing)
<br> (Fine in html5)

Inline vs block level elements:
Inline Elements: (<span>, <img>, <a>)
Do no start on a new line
Take only the necessary width/
Block Elements: (<div>, <h1> - <h6>, <p>, <form>)
Start on a new line
Take full width available.

Using a link:
<a href="link"> </a>
Link with external website:
<a href="link" target="_blank"> </a>

Tag Attributes: <h1 title="My Company">content</tagname>
<tagname attributename="attributevalue">content</tagname>
All tags can have attributes
Provide information about an element
Placed within the start tag
Key/value paries (id="someld")

HTML5 Semantic Tags:
A semantic element clearly describes its meaning to both the browser and the developer.
<header></header>
<footer></footer>
<aside></aside>
<main></main>
<article></article>
<nav></nav>
<section></section>
<details></details>

